138static bool rendererNeedsDeferredUpdate(const RenderObject& renderer)
139{
140 ASSERT(!renderer.beingDestroyed());
141 auto& document = renderer.document();
142 return renderer.needsLayout() || document.needsStyleRecalc() || document.inRenderTreeUpdate() || (document.view() && document.view()->layoutContext().isInRenderTreeLayout());
143}

145static bool nodeAndRendererAreValid(Node* node)
146{
147 if (!node)
148 return false;
149
150 auto* renderer = node->renderer();
151 return renderer && !renderer->beingDestroyed();
152}

154AccessibilityObjectInclusion AXComputedObjectAttributeCache::getIgnored(AXID id) const
155{
156 auto it = m_idMapping.find(id);
157 return it != m_idMapping.end() ? it->value.ignored : AccessibilityObjectInclusion::DefaultBehavior;
158}
159
160void AXComputedObjectAttributeCache::setIgnored(AXID id, AccessibilityObjectInclusion inclusion)
161{
162 HashMap<AXID, CachedAXObjectAttributes>::iterator it = m_idMapping.find(id);
163 if (it != m_idMapping.end())
164 it->value.ignored = inclusion;
165 else {
166 CachedAXObjectAttributes attributes;
167 attributes.ignored = inclusion;
168 m_idMapping.set(id, attributes);
169 }
170}

172AccessibilityReplacedText::AccessibilityReplacedText(const VisibleSelection& selection)
173{
174 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled()) {
175 m_replacedRange.startIndex.value = indexForVisiblePosition(selection.visibleStart(), m_replacedRange.startIndex.scope);
176 if (selection.isRange()) {
177 m_replacedText = AccessibilityObject::stringForVisiblePositionRange(selection);
178 m_replacedRange.endIndex.value = indexForVisiblePosition(selection.visibleEnd(), m_replacedRange.endIndex.scope);
179 } else
180 m_replacedRange.endIndex = m_replacedRange.startIndex;
181 }
182}
183
184void AccessibilityReplacedText::postTextStateChangeNotification(AXObjectCache* cache, AXTextEditType type, const String& text, const VisibleSelection& selection)
185{
186 if (!cache)
187 return;
188 if (!AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled())
189 return;
190
191 VisiblePosition position = selection.start();
192 auto* node = highestEditableRoot(position.deepEquivalent(), HasEditableAXRole);
193 if (m_replacedText.length())
194 cache->postTextReplacementNotification(node, AXTextEditTypeDelete, m_replacedText, type, text, position);
195 else
196 cache->postTextStateChangeNotification(node, type, text, position);
197}

235AXObjectCache::~AXObjectCache()
236{
237 m_notificationPostTimer.stop();
238 m_liveRegionChangedPostTimer.stop();
239 m_focusModalNodeTimer.stop();
240 m_performCacheUpdateTimer.stop();
241
242 for (const auto& object : m_objects.values())
243 object->detach(AccessibilityDetachmentType::CacheDestroyed);
244
245#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY_ISOLATED_TREE)
246 if (m_pageID)
247 AXIsolatedTree::removeTreeForPageID(*m_pageID);
248#endif
249}

251void AXObjectCache::findModalNodes()
252{
253 // Traverse the DOM tree to look for the aria-modal=true nodes.
254 for (Element* element = ElementTraversal::firstWithin(document().rootNode()); element; element = ElementTraversal::nextIncludingPseudo(*element)) {
255 // Must have dialog or alertdialog role
256 if (!nodeHasRole(element, "dialog") && !nodeHasRole(element, "alertdialog"))
257 continue;
258 if (!equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(element->attributeWithoutSynchronization(aria_modalAttr), "true"))
259 continue;
260
261 m_modalElementsSet.add(element);
262 }
263
264 m_modalNodesInitialized = true;
265}
266
267Element* AXObjectCache::currentModalNode()
268{
269 // There might be multiple nodes with aria-modal=true set.
270 // We use this function to pick the one we want.
271 m_currentModalElement = nullptr;
272 if (m_modalElementsSet.isEmpty())
273 return nullptr;
274
275 // If any of the modal nodes contains the keyboard focus, we want to pick that one.
276 // If not, we want to pick the last visible dialog in the DOM.
277 RefPtr<Element> focusedElement = document().focusedElement();
278 RefPtr<Element> lastVisible;
279 for (auto& element : m_modalElementsSet) {
280 if (isNodeVisible(element)) {
281 if (focusedElement && focusedElement->isDescendantOf(element)) {
282 m_currentModalElement = makeWeakPtr(element);
283 break;
284 }
285
286 lastVisible = element;
287 }
288 }
289
290 if (!m_currentModalElement)
291 m_currentModalElement = makeWeakPtr(lastVisible.get());
292
293 return m_currentModalElement.get();
294}
295
296bool AXObjectCache::isNodeVisible(Node* node) const
297{
298 if (!is<Element>(node))
299 return false;
300
301 RenderObject* renderer = node->renderer();
302 if (!renderer)
303 return false;
304
305 const auto& style = renderer->style();
306 if (style.display() == DisplayType::None)
307 return false;
308
309 auto* renderLayer = renderer->enclosingLayer();
310 if (style.visibility() != Visibility::Visible && renderLayer && !renderLayer->hasVisibleContent())
311 return false;
312
313 // Check whether this object or any of its ancestors has opacity 0.
314 // The resulting opacity of a RenderObject is computed as the multiplication
315 // of its opacity times the opacities of its ancestors.
316 for (auto* renderObject = renderer; renderObject; renderObject = renderObject->parent()) {
317 if (!renderObject->style().opacity())
318 return false;
319 }
320
321 // We also need to consider aria hidden status.
322 if (!isNodeAriaVisible(node))
323 return false;
324
325 return true;
326}
327
328// This function returns the valid aria modal node.
329Node* AXObjectCache::modalNode()
330{
331 if (!m_modalNodesInitialized)
332 findModalNodes();
333
334 if (m_modalElementsSet.isEmpty())
335 return nullptr;
336
337 // Check the cached current valid aria modal node first.
338 // Usually when one dialog sets aria-modal=true, that dialog is the one we want.
339 if (isNodeVisible(m_currentModalElement.get()))
340 return m_currentModalElement.get();
341
342 // Recompute the valid aria modal node when m_currentModalElement is null or hidden.
343 return currentModalNode();
344}

346AccessibilityObject* AXObjectCache::focusedImageMapUIElement(HTMLAreaElement* areaElement)
347{
348 // Find the corresponding accessibility object for the HTMLAreaElement. This should be
349 // in the list of children for its corresponding image.
350 if (!areaElement)
351 return nullptr;
352
353 HTMLImageElement* imageElement = areaElement->imageElement();
354 if (!imageElement)
355 return nullptr;
356
357 AccessibilityObject* axRenderImage = areaElement->document().axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(imageElement);
358 if (!axRenderImage)
359 return nullptr;
360
361 for (const auto& child : axRenderImage->children()) {
362 if (!is<AccessibilityImageMapLink>(*child))
363 continue;
364
365 if (downcast<AccessibilityImageMapLink>(*child).areaElement() == areaElement)
366 return downcast<AccessibilityImageMapLink>(child.get());
367 }
368
369 return nullptr;
370}

372AXCoreObject* AXObjectCache::focusedObjectForPage(const Page* page)
373{
374 ASSERT(isMainThread());
375
376 if (!gAccessibilityEnabled)
377 return nullptr;
378
379 // get the focused node in the page
380 Document* document = page->focusController().focusedOrMainFrame().document();
381 if (!document)
382 return nullptr;
383
384 document->updateStyleIfNeeded();
385
386 Element* focusedElement = document->focusedElement();
387 if (is<HTMLAreaElement>(focusedElement))
388 return focusedImageMapUIElement(downcast<HTMLAreaElement>(focusedElement));
389
390 auto* axObjectCache = document->axObjectCache();
391 if (!axObjectCache)
392 return nullptr;
393
394 AXCoreObject* focus = axObjectCache->getOrCreate(focusedElement ? focusedElement : static_cast<Node*>(document));
395 if (!focus)
396 return nullptr;
397
398 if (focus->shouldFocusActiveDescendant()) {
399 if (auto* descendant = focus->activeDescendant())
400 focus = descendant;
401 }
402
403 // the HTML element, for example, is focusable but has an AX object that is ignored
404 if (focus->accessibilityIsIgnored())
405 focus = focus->parentObjectUnignored();
406
407 return focus;
408}

421void AXObjectCache::setIsolatedTreeFocusedObject(Node* focusedNode)
422{
423 ASSERT(isMainThread());
424 if (!m_pageID)
425 return;
426
427 auto* focus = getOrCreate(focusedNode);
428
429 if (auto tree = AXIsolatedTree::treeForPageID(*m_pageID))
430 tree->setFocusedNodeID(focus ? focus->objectID() : InvalidAXID);
431}
432#endif

434AXCoreObject* AXObjectCache::focusedUIElementForPage(const Page* page)
435{
436#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY_ISOLATED_TREE)
437 if (isIsolatedTreeEnabled())
438 return isolatedTreeFocusedObject();
439#endif
440
441 return focusedObjectForPage(page);

444AccessibilityObject* AXObjectCache::get(Widget* widget)
445{
446 if (!widget)
447 return nullptr;
448
449 AXID axID = m_widgetObjectMapping.get(widget);
450 ASSERT(!HashTraits<AXID>::isDeletedValue(axID));
451 if (!axID)
452 return nullptr;
453
454 return m_objects.get(axID);
455}

457AccessibilityObject* AXObjectCache::get(RenderObject* renderer)
458{
459 if (!renderer)
460 return nullptr;
461
462 AXID axID = m_renderObjectMapping.get(renderer);
463 ASSERT(!HashTraits<AXID>::isDeletedValue(axID));
464 if (!axID)
465 return nullptr;
466
467 return m_objects.get(axID);
468}
469
470AccessibilityObject* AXObjectCache::get(Node* node)
471{
472 if (!node)
473 return nullptr;
474
475 AXID renderID = node->renderer() ? m_renderObjectMapping.get(node->renderer()) : 0;
476 ASSERT(!HashTraits<AXID>::isDeletedValue(renderID));
477
478 AXID nodeID = m_nodeObjectMapping.get(node);
479 ASSERT(!HashTraits<AXID>::isDeletedValue(nodeID));
480
481 if (node->renderer() && nodeID && !renderID) {
482 // This can happen if an AccessibilityNodeObject is created for a node that's not
483 // rendered, but later something changes and it gets a renderer (like if it's
484 // reparented).
485 remove(nodeID);
486 return nullptr;
487 }
488
489 if (renderID)
490 return m_objects.get(renderID);
491
492 if (!nodeID)
493 return nullptr;
494
495 return m_objects.get(nodeID);
496}

498// FIXME: This probably belongs on Node.
499// FIXME: This should take a const char*, but one caller passes nullAtom().
500bool nodeHasRole(Node* node, const String& role)
501{
502 if (!node || !is<Element>(node))
503 return false;
504
505 auto& roleValue = downcast<Element>(*node).attributeWithoutSynchronization(roleAttr);
506 if (role.isNull())
507 return roleValue.isEmpty();
508 if (roleValue.isEmpty())
509 return false;
510
511 return SpaceSplitString(roleValue, true).contains(role);
512}
513
514static bool isSimpleImage(const RenderObject& renderer)
515{
516 if (!is<RenderImage>(renderer))
517 return false;
518
519 // Exclude ImageButtons because they are treated as buttons, not as images.
520 auto* node = renderer.node();
521 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(node))
522 return false;
523
524 // ImageMaps are not simple images.
525 if (downcast<RenderImage>(renderer).imageMap()
526 || (is<HTMLImageElement>(node) && downcast<HTMLImageElement>(node)->hasAttributeWithoutSynchronization(usemapAttr)))
527 return false;
528
529 // Exclude video and audio elements.
530 if (is<HTMLMediaElement>(node))
531 return false;
532
533 return true;
534}

536static Ref<AccessibilityObject> createFromRenderer(RenderObject* renderer)
537{
538 // FIXME: How could renderer->node() ever not be an Element?
539 Node* node = renderer->node();
540
541 // If the node is aria role="list" or the aria role is empty and its a
542 // ul/ol/dl type (it shouldn't be a list if aria says otherwise).
543 if (node && ((nodeHasRole(node, "list") || nodeHasRole(node, "directory"))
544 || (nodeHasRole(node, nullAtom()) && (node->hasTagName(ulTag) || node->hasTagName(olTag) || node->hasTagName(dlTag)))))
545 return AccessibilityList::create(renderer);
546
547 // aria tables
548 if (nodeHasRole(node, "grid") || nodeHasRole(node, "treegrid") || nodeHasRole(node, "table"))
549 return AccessibilityARIAGrid::create(renderer);
550 if (nodeHasRole(node, "row"))
551 return AccessibilityARIAGridRow::create(renderer);
552 if (nodeHasRole(node, "gridcell") || nodeHasRole(node, "cell") || nodeHasRole(node, "columnheader") || nodeHasRole(node, "rowheader"))
553 return AccessibilityARIAGridCell::create(renderer);
554
555 // aria tree
556 if (nodeHasRole(node, "tree"))
557 return AccessibilityTree::create(renderer);
558 if (nodeHasRole(node, "treeitem"))
559 return AccessibilityTreeItem::create(renderer);
560
561 if (node && is<HTMLLabelElement>(node) && nodeHasRole(node, nullAtom()))
562 return AccessibilityLabel::create(renderer);
563
564#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
565 if (is<HTMLMediaElement>(node) && nodeHasRole(node, nullAtom()))
566 return AccessibilityMediaObject::create(renderer);
567#endif
568
569 if (is<RenderSVGRoot>(*renderer))
570 return AccessibilitySVGRoot::create(renderer);
571
572 if (is<SVGElement>(node))
573 return AccessibilitySVGElement::create(renderer);
574
575 if (isSimpleImage(*renderer))
576 return AXImage::create(downcast<RenderImage>(renderer));
577
578#if ENABLE(MATHML)
579 // The mfenced element creates anonymous RenderMathMLOperators which should be treated
580 // as MathML elements and assigned the MathElementRole so that platform logic regarding
581 // inclusion and role mapping is not bypassed.
582 bool isAnonymousOperator = renderer->isAnonymous() && is<RenderMathMLOperator>(*renderer);
583 if (isAnonymousOperator || is<MathMLElement>(node))
584 return AccessibilityMathMLElement::create(renderer, isAnonymousOperator);
585#endif
586
587 if (is<RenderBoxModelObject>(*renderer)) {
588 RenderBoxModelObject& cssBox = downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(*renderer);
589 if (is<RenderListBox>(cssBox))
590 return AccessibilityListBox::create(&downcast<RenderListBox>(cssBox));
591 if (is<RenderMenuList>(cssBox))
592 return AccessibilityMenuList::create(&downcast<RenderMenuList>(cssBox));
593
594 // standard tables
595 if (is<RenderTable>(cssBox))
596 return AccessibilityTable::create(&downcast<RenderTable>(cssBox));
597 if (is<RenderTableRow>(cssBox))
598 return AccessibilityTableRow::create(&downcast<RenderTableRow>(cssBox));
599 if (is<RenderTableCell>(cssBox))
600 return AccessibilityTableCell::create(&downcast<RenderTableCell>(cssBox));
601
602 // progress bar
603 if (is<RenderProgress>(cssBox))
604 return AccessibilityProgressIndicator::create(&downcast<RenderProgress>(cssBox));
605
606#if ENABLE(ATTACHMENT_ELEMENT)
607 if (is<RenderAttachment>(cssBox))
608 return AccessibilityAttachment::create(&downcast<RenderAttachment>(cssBox));
609#endif
610
611 if (is<RenderMeter>(cssBox))
612 return AccessibilityProgressIndicator::create(&downcast<RenderMeter>(cssBox));
613
614 // input type=range
615 if (is<RenderSlider>(cssBox))
616 return AccessibilitySlider::create(&downcast<RenderSlider>(cssBox));
617 }
618
619 return AccessibilityRenderObject::create(renderer);
620}

622static Ref<AccessibilityObject> createFromNode(Node* node)
623{
624 return AccessibilityNodeObject::create(node);
625}

627void AXObjectCache::cacheAndInitializeWrapper(AccessibilityObject* newObject, DOMObjectVariant domObject)
628{
629 ASSERT(newObject);
630 AXID axID = getAXID(newObject);
631 ASSERT(axID != InvalidAXID);
632
633 WTF::switchOn(domObject,
634 [&axID, this] (RenderObject* typedValue) { m_renderObjectMapping.set(typedValue, axID); },
635 [&axID, this] (Node* typedValue) { m_nodeObjectMapping.set(typedValue, axID); },
636 [&axID, this] (Widget* typedValue) { m_widgetObjectMapping.set(typedValue, axID); },
637 [] (auto&) { }
638 );
639
640 m_objects.set(axID, newObject);
641 newObject->init();
642 attachWrapper(newObject);
643}
644
645AccessibilityObject* AXObjectCache::getOrCreate(Widget* widget)
646{
647 if (!widget)
648 return nullptr;
649
650 if (AccessibilityObject* obj = get(widget))
651 return obj;
652
653 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> newObj;
654 if (is<ScrollView>(*widget))
655 newObj = AccessibilityScrollView::create(downcast<ScrollView>(widget));
656 else if (is<Scrollbar>(*widget))
657 newObj = AccessibilityScrollbar::create(downcast<Scrollbar>(widget));
658
659 // Will crash later if we have two objects for the same widget.
660 ASSERT(!get(widget));
661
662 // Catch the case if an (unsupported) widget type is used. Only FrameView and ScrollBar are supported now.
663 ASSERT(newObj);
664 if (!newObj)
665 return nullptr;
666
667 cacheAndInitializeWrapper(newObj.get(), widget);
668 return newObj.get();
669}
670
671AccessibilityObject* AXObjectCache::getOrCreate(Node* node)
672{
673 if (!node)
674 return nullptr;
675
676 if (AccessibilityObject* obj = get(node))
677 return obj;
678
679 if (node->renderer())
680 return getOrCreate(node->renderer());
681
682 if (!node->parentElement())
683 return nullptr;
684
685 bool isOptionElement = is<HTMLOptionElement>(*node);
686 if (isOptionElement || is<HTMLOptGroupElement>(*node)) {
687 auto select = isOptionElement
688 ? downcast<HTMLOptionElement>(*node).ownerSelectElement()
689 : downcast<HTMLOptGroupElement>(*node).ownerSelectElement();
690 if (!select)
691 return nullptr;
692 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> object;
693 if (select->usesMenuList()) {
694 if (!isOptionElement)
695 return nullptr;
696 object = AccessibilityMenuListOption::create(downcast<HTMLOptionElement>(*node));
697 } else
698 object = AccessibilityListBoxOption::create(downcast<HTMLElement>(*node));
699 cacheAndInitializeWrapper(object.get(), node);
700 return object.get();
701 }
702
703 // It's only allowed to create an AccessibilityObject from a Node if it's in a canvas subtree.
704 // Or if it's a hidden element, but we still want to expose it because of other ARIA attributes.
705 bool inCanvasSubtree = lineageOfType<HTMLCanvasElement>(*node->parentElement()).first();
706 bool isHidden = isNodeAriaVisible(node);
707
708 bool insideMeterElement = is<HTMLMeterElement>(*node->parentElement());
709
710 if (!inCanvasSubtree && !isHidden && !insideMeterElement)
711 return nullptr;
712
713 auto protectedNode = makeRef(*node);
714
715 // Fallback content is only focusable as long as the canvas is displayed and visible.
716 // Update the style before Element::isFocusable() gets called.
717 if (inCanvasSubtree)
718 node->document().updateStyleIfNeeded();
719
720 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> newObj = createFromNode(node);
721
722 // Will crash later if we have two objects for the same node.
723 ASSERT(!get(node));
724
725 cacheAndInitializeWrapper(newObj.get(), node);
726 newObj->setLastKnownIsIgnoredValue(newObj->accessibilityIsIgnored());
727 // Sometimes asking accessibilityIsIgnored() will cause the newObject to be deallocated, and then
728 // it will disappear when this function is finished, leading to a use-after-free.
729 if (newObj->isDetached())
730 return nullptr;
731
732 return newObj.get();
733}
734
735AccessibilityObject* AXObjectCache::getOrCreate(RenderObject* renderer)
736{
737 if (!renderer)
738 return nullptr;
739
740 if (AccessibilityObject* obj = get(renderer))
741 return obj;
742
743 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> newObj = createFromRenderer(renderer);
744
745 // Will crash later if we have two objects for the same renderer.
746 ASSERT(!get(renderer));
747
748 cacheAndInitializeWrapper(newObj.get(), renderer);
749 newObj->setLastKnownIsIgnoredValue(newObj->accessibilityIsIgnored());
750 // Sometimes asking accessibilityIsIgnored() will cause the newObject to be deallocated, and then
751 // it will disappear when this function is finished, leading to a use-after-free.
752 if (newObj->isDetached())
753 return nullptr;
754
755 return newObj.get();
756}

762 return client == kAXClientTypeVoiceOver
763 || UNLIKELY(client == kAXClientTypeWebKitTesting);

765
766bool AXObjectCache::isIsolatedTreeEnabled()
767{
768 static std::atomic<bool> enabled { false };
769 if (enabled)
770 return true;
771
772 if (!isMainThread()) {
773 ASSERT(_AXUIElementRequestServicedBySecondaryAXThread());
774 enabled = true;
775 } else {
776 enabled = RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().isAccessibilityIsolatedTreeEnabled() // Used to turn off in apps other than Safari, e.g., Mail.
777 && _AXSIsolatedTreeModeFunctionIsAvailable()
778 && _AXSIsolatedTreeMode_Soft() != AXSIsolatedTreeModeOff // Used to switch via system defaults.
779 && clientSupportsIsolatedTree();
780 }
781
782 return enabled;
783}

854AccessibilityObject* AXObjectCache::create(AccessibilityRole role)
855{
856 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> obj;
857
858 // will be filled in...
859 switch (role) {
860 case AccessibilityRole::ImageMapLink:
861 obj = AccessibilityImageMapLink::create();
862 break;
863 case AccessibilityRole::Column:
864 obj = AccessibilityTableColumn::create();
865 break;
866 case AccessibilityRole::TableHeaderContainer:
867 obj = AccessibilityTableHeaderContainer::create();
868 break;
869 case AccessibilityRole::SliderThumb:
870 obj = AccessibilitySliderThumb::create();
871 break;
872 case AccessibilityRole::MenuListPopup:
873 obj = AccessibilityMenuListPopup::create();
874 break;
875 case AccessibilityRole::SpinButton:
876 obj = AccessibilitySpinButton::create();
877 break;
878 case AccessibilityRole::SpinButtonPart:
879 obj = AccessibilitySpinButtonPart::create();
880 break;
881 default:
882 obj = nullptr;
883 }
884
885 if (!obj)
886 return nullptr;
887
888 cacheAndInitializeWrapper(obj.get());
889 return obj.get();
890}

892void AXObjectCache::remove(AXID axID)
893{
894 AXTRACE("AXObjectCache::remove");
895 AXLOG(makeString("AXID ", axID));
896
897 if (!axID)
898 return;
899
900#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY_ISOLATED_TREE)
901 if (m_pageID) {
902 if (auto tree = AXIsolatedTree::treeForPageID(*m_pageID))
903 tree->removeNode(axID);
904 }
905#endif
906
907 auto object = m_objects.take(axID);
908 if (!object)
909 return;
910
911 object->detach(AccessibilityDetachmentType::ElementDestroyed);
912
913 m_idsInUse.remove(axID);
914 ASSERT(m_objects.size() >= m_idsInUse.size());
915}

917void AXObjectCache::remove(RenderObject* renderer)
918{
919 if (!renderer)
920 return;
921 remove(m_renderObjectMapping.take(renderer));
922}
923
924void AXObjectCache::remove(Node& node)
925{
926 if (is<Element>(node)) {
927 m_deferredTextFormControlValue.remove(downcast<Element>(&node));
928 m_deferredAttributeChange.remove(downcast<Element>(&node));
929 m_modalElementsSet.remove(downcast<Element>(&node));
930 }
931 m_deferredChildrenChangedNodeList.remove(&node);
932 m_deferredTextChangedList.remove(&node);
933 // Remove the entry if the new focused node is being removed.
934 m_deferredFocusedNodeChange.removeAllMatching([&node](auto& entry) -> bool {
935 return entry.second == &node;
936 });
937 // Set nullptr to the old focused node if it is being removed.
938 std::for_each(m_deferredFocusedNodeChange.begin(), m_deferredFocusedNodeChange.end(), [&node](auto& entry) {
939 if (entry.first == &node)
940 entry.first = nullptr;
941 });
942
943 removeNodeForUse(node);
944
945 remove(m_nodeObjectMapping.take(&node));
946 remove(node.renderer());
947}

950{
951 if (!view)
952 return;
953 remove(m_widgetObjectMapping.take(view));
954}

959{

965 ++objID;

984AXID AXObjectCache::getAXID(AccessibilityObject* obj)
985{
986 // check for already-assigned ID

990 return objID;

1006void AXObjectCache::textChanged(AccessibilityObject* object)
1007{
1008 AXTRACE("AXObjectCache::textChanged");
1009 AXLOG(object);
1010
1011 if (!object)
1012 return;
1013
1014 // If this element supports ARIA live regions, or is part of a region with an ARIA editable role,
1015 // then notify the AT of changes.
1016 bool notifiedNonNativeTextControl = false;
1017 for (auto* parent = object; parent; parent = parent->parentObject()) {
1018 if (parent->supportsLiveRegion())
1019 postLiveRegionChangeNotification(parent);
1020
1021 if (!notifiedNonNativeTextControl && parent->isNonNativeTextControl()) {
1022 postNotification(parent, parent->document(), AXValueChanged);
1023 notifiedNonNativeTextControl = true;
1024 }
1025 }
1026
1027 postNotification(object, object->document(), AXTextChanged);
1028
1029 if (object->parentObjectIfExists())
1030 object->notifyIfIgnoredValueChanged();
1031}

1036 // an AccessibilityRenderObject, because it was reparented to a location outside of a canvas.
1037 get(node);

1092void AXObjectCache::notificationPostTimerFired()
1093{
1094 AXTRACE("AXObjectCache::notificationPostTimerFired");
1095 // During LayoutTests, accessibility may be disabled between the time the notifications are queued and the timer fires.
1096 // Thus check here and return if accessibility is disabled.
1097 if (!accessibilityEnabled())
1098 return;
1099
1100 Ref<Document> protectorForCacheOwner(m_document);
1101 m_notificationPostTimer.stop();
1102
1103 if (!m_document.hasLivingRenderTree())
1104 return;
1105
1106 // In tests, posting notifications has a tendency to immediately queue up other notifications, which can lead to unexpected behavior
1107 // when the notification list is cleared at the end. Instead copy this list at the start.
1108 auto notifications = WTFMove(m_notificationsToPost);
1109
1110 // Filter out the notifications that are not going to be posted to platform clients.
1111 Vector<std::pair<RefPtr<AXCoreObject>, AXNotification>> notificationsToPost;
1112 notificationsToPost.reserveCapacity(notifications.size());
1113 for (const auto& note : notifications) {
1114 ASSERT(note.first);
1115 if (!note.first->objectID() || !note.first->axObjectCache())
1116 continue;
1117
1118#ifndef NDEBUG
1119 // Make sure none of the render views are in the process of being layed out.
1120 // Notifications should only be sent after the renderer has finished
1121 if (is<AccessibilityRenderObject>(*note.first)) {
1122 if (auto* renderer = downcast<AccessibilityRenderObject>(*note.first).renderer())
1123 ASSERT(!renderer->view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState());
1124 }
1125#endif
1126
1127 // Ensure that this menu really is a menu. We do this check here so that we don't have to create
1128 // the axChildren when the menu is marked as opening.
1129 if (note.second == AXMenuOpened) {
1130 note.first->updateChildrenIfNecessary();
1131 if (note.first->roleValue() != AccessibilityRole::Menu)
1132 continue;
1133 }
1134
1135 if (note.second == AXChildrenChanged && note.first->parentObjectIfExists()
1136 && note.first->lastKnownIsIgnoredValue() != note.first->accessibilityIsIgnored())
1137 childrenChanged(note.first->parentObject());
1138
1139 notificationsToPost.append(note);
1140 }
1141
1142#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY_ISOLATED_TREE)
1143 updateIsolatedTree(notificationsToPost);
1144#endif
1145
1146 for (const auto& note : notificationsToPost)
1147 postPlatformNotification(note.first.get(), note.second);
1148}
1149
1150void AXObjectCache::passwordNotificationPostTimerFired()
1151{
1152#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1153 m_passwordNotificationPostTimer.stop();
1154
1155 // In tests, posting notifications has a tendency to immediately queue up other notifications, which can lead to unexpected behavior
1156 // when the notification list is cleared at the end. Instead copy this list at the start.
1157 auto notifications = WTFMove(m_passwordNotificationsToPost);
1158
1159 for (auto& notification : notifications)
1160 postTextStateChangePlatformNotification(notification.get(), AXTextEditTypeInsert, " ", VisiblePosition());
1161#endif
1162}
1163
1164void AXObjectCache::postNotification(RenderObject* renderer, AXNotification notification, PostTarget postTarget)
1165{
1166 if (!renderer)
1167 return;
1168
1169 stopCachingComputedObjectAttributes();
1170
1171 // Get an accessibility object that already exists. One should not be created here
1172 // because a render update may be in progress and creating an AX object can re-trigger a layout
1173 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> object = get(renderer);
1174 while (!object && renderer) {
1175 renderer = renderer->parent();
1176 object = get(renderer);
1177 }
1178
1179 if (!renderer)
1180 return;
1181
1182 postNotification(object.get(), &renderer->document(), notification, postTarget);
1183}
1184
1185void AXObjectCache::postNotification(Node* node, AXNotification notification, PostTarget postTarget)
1186{
1187 if (!node)
1188 return;
1189
1190 stopCachingComputedObjectAttributes();
1191
1192 // Get an accessibility object that already exists. One should not be created here
1193 // because a render update may be in progress and creating an AX object can re-trigger a layout
1194 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> object = get(node);
1195 while (!object && node) {
1196 node = node->parentNode();
1197 object = get(node);
1198 }
1199
1200 if (!node)
1201 return;
1202
1203 postNotification(object.get(), &node->document(), notification, postTarget);
1204}
1205
1206void AXObjectCache::postNotification(AXCoreObject* object, Document* document, AXNotification notification, PostTarget postTarget)
1207{
1208 AXTRACE("AXObjectCache::postNotification");
1209 AXLOG(std::make_pair(object, notification));
1210 ASSERT(isMainThread());
1211
1212 stopCachingComputedObjectAttributes();
1213
1214 if (object && postTarget == PostTarget::ObservableParent)
1215 object = object->observableObject();
1216
1217 if (!object && document)
1218 object = get(document->renderView());
1219
1220 if (!object)
1221 return;
1222
1223 m_notificationsToPost.append(std::make_pair(object, notification));
1224 if (!m_notificationPostTimer.isActive())
1225 m_notificationPostTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
1226}

1450void AXObjectCache::postTextStateChangeNotification(const Position& position, const AXTextStateChangeIntent& intent, const VisibleSelection& selection)
1451{
1452 Node* node = position.deprecatedNode();
1453 if (!node)
1454 return;
1455
1456 stopCachingComputedObjectAttributes();
1457
1458#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1459 AccessibilityObject* object = getOrCreate(node);
1460 if (object && object->accessibilityIsIgnored()) {
1461 if (position.atLastEditingPositionForNode()) {
1462 if (AccessibilityObject* nextSibling = object->nextSiblingUnignored(1))
1463 object = nextSibling;
1464 } else if (position.atFirstEditingPositionForNode()) {
1465 if (AccessibilityObject* previousSibling = object->previousSiblingUnignored(1))
1466 object = previousSibling;
1467 }
1468 }
1469
1470 postTextStateChangeNotification(object, intent, selection);
1471#else
1472 postTextStateChangeNotification(node, intent, selection);
1473#endif
1474}
1475
1476void AXObjectCache::postTextStateChangeNotification(AccessibilityObject* object, const AXTextStateChangeIntent& intent, const VisibleSelection& selection)
1477{
1478 AXTRACE("AXObjectCache::postTextStateChangeNotification");
1479 stopCachingComputedObjectAttributes();
1480
1481#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1482 if (object) {
1483 if (isPasswordFieldOrContainedByPasswordField(object))
1484 return;
1485
1486 if (auto observableObject = object->observableObject())
1487 object = observableObject;
1488 }
1489
1490 if (!object)
1491 object = rootWebArea();
1492
1493 if (object) {
1494#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY_ISOLATED_TREE)
1495 updateIsolatedTree(*object, AXSelectedTextChanged);
1496#endif
1497
1498 const AXTextStateChangeIntent& newIntent = (intent.type == AXTextStateChangeTypeUnknown || (m_isSynchronizingSelection && m_textSelectionIntent.type != AXTextStateChangeTypeUnknown)) ? m_textSelectionIntent : intent;
1499 postTextStateChangePlatformNotification(object, newIntent, selection);
1500 }
1501#else
1502 UNUSED_PARAM(object);
1503 UNUSED_PARAM(intent);
1504 UNUSED_PARAM(selection);
1505#endif
1506
1507 setTextSelectionIntent(AXTextStateChangeIntent());
1508 setIsSynchronizingSelection(false);
1509}

1511void AXObjectCache::postTextStateChangeNotification(Node* node, AXTextEditType type, const String& text, const VisiblePosition& position)
1512{

1514 if (!node || type == AXTextEditTypeUnknown)
1515 return;
1516
1517 stopCachingComputedObjectAttributes();
1518
1519 AccessibilityObject* object = getOrCreate(node);
1520#if PLATFORM(COCOA)

1531 return;

1540#endif
1541}

1588bool AXObjectCache::enqueuePasswordValueChangeNotification(AccessibilityObject* object)
1589{
1590 if (!isPasswordFieldOrContainedByPasswordField(object))
1591 return false;
1592
1593 AccessibilityObject* observableObject = object->observableObject();
1594 if (!observableObject) {
1595 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1596 // return true even though the enqueue didn't happen because this is a password field and caller shouldn't post a notification
1597 return true;
1598 }
1599
1600 m_passwordNotificationsToPost.add(observableObject);
1601 if (!m_passwordNotificationPostTimer.isActive())
1602 m_passwordNotificationPostTimer.startOneShot(accessibilityPasswordValueChangeNotificationInterval);
1603
1604 return true;
1605}

1644static AccessibilityObject* firstFocusableChild(AccessibilityObject* obj)
1645{
1646 if (!obj)
1647 return nullptr;
1648
1649 for (auto* child = obj->firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
1650 if (child->canSetFocusAttribute())
1651 return child;
1652 if (AccessibilityObject* focusable = firstFocusableChild(child))
1653 return focusable;
1654 }
1655 return nullptr;
1656}

1666void AXObjectCache::focusModalNodeTimerFired()
1667{
1668 if (!m_document.hasLivingRenderTree())
1669 return;
1670
1671 Ref<Document> protectedDocument(m_document);
1672 if (!nodeAndRendererAreValid(m_currentModalElement.get()) || !isNodeVisible(m_currentModalElement.get()))
1673 return;
1674
1675 // Don't set focus if we are already focusing onto some element within
1676 // the dialog.
1677 if (m_currentModalElement->contains(document().focusedElement()))
1678 return;
1679
1680 if (AccessibilityObject* currentModalNodeObject = getOrCreate(m_currentModalElement.get())) {
1681 if (AccessibilityObject* focusable = firstFocusableChild(currentModalNodeObject))
1682 focusable->setFocused(true);
1683 }

1698void AXObjectCache::handleAriaExpandedChange(Node* node)
1699{
1700 // An aria-expanded change can cause two notifications to be posted:
1701 // RowCountChanged for the tree or table ancestor of this object, and
1702 // RowExpanded/Collapsed for this object.
1703 if (auto object = makeRefPtr(get(node))) {
1704 // Find the ancestor that supports RowCountChanged if exists.
1705 auto* ancestor = Accessibility::findAncestor<AccessibilityObject>(*object, false, [] (auto& candidate) {
1706 return candidate.supportsRowCountChange();
1707 });
1708
1709 // Post that the ancestor's row count changed.
1710 if (ancestor)
1711 postNotification(ancestor, &document(), AXRowCountChanged);
1712
1713 // Post that the specific row either collapsed or expanded.
1714 auto role = object->roleValue();
1715 if (role == AccessibilityRole::Row || role == AccessibilityRole::TreeItem)
1716 postNotification(object.get(), &document(), object->isExpanded() ? AXRowExpanded : AXRowCollapsed);
1717 else
1718 postNotification(object.get(), &document(), AXExpandedChanged);
1719 }
1720}

1728void AXObjectCache::handleAriaRoleChanged(Node* node)

1731

1733 if (auto* obj = get(node)) {
1734 obj->updateAccessibilityRole();
1735
1736#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY_ISOLATED_TREE)
1737 updateIsolatedTree(obj, AXObjectCache::AXAriaRoleChanged);
1738#endif
1739
1740 obj->notifyIfIgnoredValueChanged();
1741 }

1744void AXObjectCache::deferAttributeChangeIfNeeded(const QualifiedName& attrName, Element* element)
1745{
1746 if (nodeAndRendererAreValid(element) && rendererNeedsDeferredUpdate(*element->renderer())) {
1747 m_deferredAttributeChange.add(element, attrName);
1748 if (!m_performCacheUpdateTimer.isActive())
1749 m_performCacheUpdateTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
1750 }
1751 else
1752 handleAttributeChange(attrName, element);
1753}
1754
1755bool AXObjectCache::shouldProcessAttributeChange(const QualifiedName& attrName, Element* element)
1756{
1757 if (!element)
1758 return false;
1759
1760 // aria-modal ends up affecting sub-trees that are being shown/hidden so it's likely that
1761 // an AT would not have accessed this node yet.
1762 if (attrName == aria_modalAttr)
1763 return true;
1764
1765 // If an AXObject has yet to be created, then there's no need to process attribute changes.
1766 // Some of these notifications are processed on the parent, so allow that to proceed as well
1767 if (get(element) || get(element->parentNode()))
1768 return true;
1769
1770 return false;
1771}
1772
1773void AXObjectCache::handleAttributeChange(const QualifiedName& attrName, Element* element)
1774{
1775 if (!shouldProcessAttributeChange(attrName, element))
1776 return;
1777
1778 if (attrName == roleAttr)
1779 handleAriaRoleChanged(element);
1780 else if (attrName == altAttr || attrName == titleAttr)
1781 textChanged(element);
1782 else if (attrName == forAttr && is<HTMLLabelElement>(*element))
1783 labelChanged(element);
1784 else if (attrName == tabindexAttr)
1785 childrenChanged(element->parentNode(), element);
1786#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY_ISOLATED_TREE)
1787 else if (attrName == langAttr)
1788 updateIsolatedTree(get(element), AXObjectCache::AXLanguageChanged);
1789 else if (attrName == idAttr)
1790 updateIsolatedTree(get(element), AXObjectCache::AXIdAttributeChanged);
1791#endif
1792
1793 if (!attrName.localName().string().startsWith("aria-"))
1794 return;
1795
1796 if (attrName == aria_activedescendantAttr)
1797 handleActiveDescendantChanged(element);
1798 else if (attrName == aria_busyAttr)
1799 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXElementBusyChanged);
1800 else if (attrName == aria_valuenowAttr || attrName == aria_valuetextAttr)
1801 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXValueChanged);
1802 else if (attrName == aria_labelAttr || attrName == aria_labeledbyAttr || attrName == aria_labelledbyAttr)
1803 textChanged(element);
1804 else if (attrName == aria_checkedAttr)
1805 checkedStateChanged(element);
1806 else if (attrName == aria_selectedAttr)
1807 selectedChildrenChanged(element);
1808 else if (attrName == aria_expandedAttr)
1809 handleAriaExpandedChange(element);
1810 else if (attrName == aria_hiddenAttr) {
1811 childrenChanged(element->parentNode(), element);
1812 if (m_currentModalElement && m_currentModalElement->isDescendantOf(element)) {
1813 m_modalNodesInitialized = false;
1814 deferModalChange(m_currentModalElement.get());
1815 }
1816 }
1817 else if (attrName == aria_invalidAttr)
1818 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXInvalidStatusChanged);
1819 else if (attrName == aria_modalAttr)
1820 deferModalChange(element);
1821 else if (attrName == aria_currentAttr)
1822 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXCurrentStateChanged);
1823 else if (attrName == aria_disabledAttr)
1824 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXDisabledStateChanged);
1825 else if (attrName == aria_pressedAttr)
1826 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXPressedStateChanged);
1827 else if (attrName == aria_readonlyAttr)
1828 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXReadOnlyStatusChanged);
1829 else if (attrName == aria_requiredAttr)
1830 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXRequiredStatusChanged);
1831 else if (attrName == aria_sortAttr)
1832 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXSortDirectionChanged);
1833 else
1834 postNotification(element, AXObjectCache::AXAriaAttributeChanged);
1835}
1836
1837void AXObjectCache::handleModalChange(Element& element)
1838{
1839 if (!nodeHasRole(&element, "dialog") && !nodeHasRole(&element, "alertdialog"))
1840 return;
1841
1842 stopCachingComputedObjectAttributes();
1843
1844 if (!m_modalNodesInitialized)
1845 findModalNodes();
1846
1847 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(element.attributeWithoutSynchronization(aria_modalAttr), "true")) {
1848 // Add the newly modified node to the modal nodes set.
1849 // We will recompute the current valid aria modal node in modalNode() when this node is not visible.
1850 m_modalElementsSet.add(&element);
1851 } else {
1852 // Remove the node from the modal nodes set.
1853 m_modalElementsSet.remove(&element);
1854 }
1855
1856 // Find new active modal node.
1857 currentModalNode();
1858
1859 if (m_currentModalElement)
1860 focusModalNode();
1861
1862 startCachingComputedObjectAttributesUntilTreeMutates();
1863}

1868 auto correspondingControl = downcast<HTMLLabelElement>(*element).control();
1869 deferTextChangedIfNeeded(correspondingControl.get());
1870}

1895VisiblePosition AXObjectCache::visiblePositionForTextMarkerData(TextMarkerData& textMarkerData)
1896{
1897 if (!isNodeInUse(textMarkerData.node)
1898 || textMarkerData.node->isPseudoElement())
1899 return { };
1900
1901 auto visiblePosition = VisiblePosition(makeContainerOffsetPosition(textMarkerData.node, textMarkerData.offset), textMarkerData.affinity);
1902 auto deepPosition = visiblePosition.deepEquivalent();
1903 if (deepPosition.isNull())
1904 return { };
1905
1906 auto* renderer = deepPosition.deprecatedNode()->renderer();
1907 if (!renderer)
1908 return { };
1909
1910 auto* cache = renderer->document().axObjectCache();
1911 if (cache && !cache->m_idsInUse.contains(textMarkerData.axID))
1912 return { };
1913
1914 return visiblePosition;
1915}
1916
1917CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::characterOffsetForTextMarkerData(TextMarkerData& textMarkerData)
1918{
1919 if (!isNodeInUse(textMarkerData.node))
1920 return CharacterOffset();
1921
1922 if (textMarkerData.ignored)
1923 return CharacterOffset();
1924
1925 CharacterOffset result = CharacterOffset(textMarkerData.node, textMarkerData.characterStartIndex, textMarkerData.characterOffset);
1926 // When we are at a line wrap and the VisiblePosition is upstream, it means the text marker is at the end of the previous line.
1927 // We use the previous CharacterOffset so that it will match the Range.
1928 if (textMarkerData.affinity == Affinity::Upstream)
1929 return previousCharacterOffset(result, false);
1930 return result;
1931}
1932
1933CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::traverseToOffsetInRange(const SimpleRange& range, int offset, TraverseOption option, bool stayWithinRange)
1934{
1935 bool toNodeEnd = option & TraverseOptionToNodeEnd;
1936 bool validateOffset = option & TraverseOptionValidateOffset;
1937 bool doNotEnterTextControls = option & TraverseOptionDoNotEnterTextControls;
1938
1939 int offsetInCharacter = 0;
1940 int cumulativeOffset = 0;
1941 int remaining = 0;
1942 int lastLength = 0;
1943 Node* currentNode = nullptr;
1944 bool finished = false;
1945 int lastStartOffset = 0;
1946
1947 TextIteratorBehaviors behaviors;
1948 if (!doNotEnterTextControls)
1949 behaviors.add(TextIteratorBehavior::EntersTextControls);
1950 TextIterator iterator(range, behaviors);
1951
1952 // When the range has zero length, there might be replaced node or brTag that we need to increment the characterOffset.
1953 if (iterator.atEnd()) {
1954 currentNode = range.start.container.ptr();
1955 lastStartOffset = range.start.offset;
1956 if (offset > 0 || toNodeEnd) {
1957 if (AccessibilityObject::replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(currentNode) || (currentNode->renderer() && currentNode->renderer()->isBR()))
1958 cumulativeOffset++;
1959 lastLength = cumulativeOffset;
1960
1961 // When going backwards, stayWithinRange is false.
1962 // Here when we don't have any character to move and we are going backwards, we traverse to the previous node.
1963 if (!lastLength && toNodeEnd && !stayWithinRange) {
1964 if (Node* preNode = previousNode(currentNode))
1965 return traverseToOffsetInRange(rangeForNodeContents(*preNode), offset, option);
1966 return CharacterOffset();
1967 }
1968 }
1969 }
1970
1971 // Sometimes text contents in a node are split into several iterations, so that iterator.range().startOffset()
1972 // might not be the total character count. Here we use a previousNode object to keep track of that.
1973 Node* previousNode = nullptr;
1974 for (; !iterator.atEnd(); iterator.advance()) {
1975 int currentLength = iterator.text().length();
1976 bool hasReplacedNodeOrBR = false;
1977
1978 Node& node = iterator.range().start.container;
1979 currentNode = &node;
1980
1981 // When currentLength == 0, we check if there's any replaced node.
1982 // If not, we skip the node with no length.
1983 if (!currentLength) {
1984 Node* childNode = iterator.node();
1985 if (AccessibilityObject::replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(childNode)) {
1986 cumulativeOffset++;
1987 currentLength++;
1988 currentNode = childNode;
1989 hasReplacedNodeOrBR = true;
1990 } else
1991 continue;
1992 } else {
1993 // Ignore space, new line, tag node.
1994 if (currentLength == 1) {
1995 if (isHTMLSpace(iterator.text()[0])) {
1996 // If the node has BR tag, we want to set the currentNode to it.
1997 Node* childNode = iterator.node();
1998 if (childNode && childNode->renderer() && childNode->renderer()->isBR()) {
1999 currentNode = childNode;
2000 hasReplacedNodeOrBR = true;
2001 } else if (auto* shadowHost = currentNode->shadowHost()) {
2002 // Since we are entering text controls, we should set the currentNode
2003 // to be the shadow host when there's no content.
2004 if (nodeIsTextControl(shadowHost) && currentNode->isShadowRoot()) {
2005 currentNode = shadowHost;
2006 continue;
2007 }
2008 } else if (previousNode && previousNode->isTextNode() && previousNode->isDescendantOf(currentNode) && currentNode->hasTagName(pTag)) {
2009 // TextIterator is emitting an extra newline after the <p> element. We should
2010 // ignore that since the extra text node is not in the DOM tree.
2011 currentNode = previousNode;
2012 continue;
2013 } else if (currentNode != previousNode) {
2014 // We should set the start offset and length for the current node in case this is the last iteration.
2015 lastStartOffset = 1;
2016 lastLength = 0;
2017 continue;
2018 }
2019 }
2020 }
2021 cumulativeOffset += currentLength;
2022 }
2023
2024 if (currentNode == previousNode) {
2025 lastLength += currentLength;
2026 lastStartOffset = iterator.range().end.offset - lastLength;
2027 } else {
2028 lastLength = currentLength;
2029 lastStartOffset = hasReplacedNodeOrBR ? 0 : iterator.range().start.offset;
2030 }
2031
2032 // Break early if we have advanced enough characters.
2033 bool offsetLimitReached = validateOffset ? cumulativeOffset + lastStartOffset >= offset : cumulativeOffset >= offset;
2034 if (!toNodeEnd && offsetLimitReached) {
2035 offsetInCharacter = validateOffset ? std::max(offset - lastStartOffset, 0) : offset - (cumulativeOffset - lastLength);
2036 finished = true;
2037 break;
2038 }
2039 previousNode = currentNode;
2040 }
2041
2042 if (!finished) {
2043 offsetInCharacter = lastLength;
2044 if (!toNodeEnd)
2045 remaining = offset - cumulativeOffset;
2046 }
2047
2048 // Sometimes when we are getting the end CharacterOffset of a line range, the TextIterator will emit an extra space at the end
2049 // and make the character count greater than the Range's end offset.
2050 if (toNodeEnd && currentNode->isTextNode() && currentNode == range.end.container.ptr() && static_cast<int>(range.end.offset) < lastStartOffset + offsetInCharacter)
2051 offsetInCharacter = range.end.offset - lastStartOffset;
2052
2053 return CharacterOffset(currentNode, lastStartOffset, offsetInCharacter, remaining);
2054}
2055
2056int AXObjectCache::lengthForRange(const std::optional<SimpleRange>& range)
2057{
2058 if (!range)
2059 return -1;
2060 int length = 0;
2061 for (TextIterator it(*range); !it.atEnd(); it.advance()) {
2062 // non-zero length means textual node, zero length means replaced node (AKA "attachments" in AX)
2063 if (it.text().length())
2064 length += it.text().length();
2065 else {
2066 // locate the node and starting offset for this replaced range
2067 if (AccessibilityObject::replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(it.node()))
2068 ++length;
2069 }
2070 }
2071 return length;
2072}
2073
2074SimpleRange AXObjectCache::rangeForNodeContents(Node& node)
2075{
2076 if (AccessibilityObject::replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(&node)) {
2077 // For replaced nodes without children, the node itself is included in the range.
2078 if (auto range = makeRangeSelectingNode(node))
2079 return *range;
2080 }
2081 return makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(node);
2082}
2083
2084std::optional<SimpleRange> AXObjectCache::rangeMatchesTextNearRange(const SimpleRange& originalRange, const String& matchText)
2085{
2086 // Create a large enough range to find the text within it that's being searched for.
2087 unsigned textLength = matchText.length();
2088 auto startPosition = VisiblePosition(makeContainerOffsetPosition(originalRange.start));
2089 for (unsigned k = 0; k < textLength; k++) {
2090 auto testPosition = startPosition.previous();
2091 if (testPosition.isNull())
2092 break;
2093 startPosition = testPosition;
2094 }
2095
2096 auto endPosition = VisiblePosition(makeContainerOffsetPosition(originalRange.end));
2097 for (unsigned k = 0; k < textLength; k++) {
2098 auto testPosition = endPosition.next();
2099 if (testPosition.isNull())
2100 break;
2101 endPosition = testPosition;
2102 }
2103
2104 auto searchRange = makeSimpleRange(startPosition, endPosition);
2105 if (!searchRange || searchRange->collapsed())
2106 return std::nullopt;
2107
2108 auto targetOffset = characterCount({ searchRange->start, originalRange.start }, TextIteratorBehavior::EmitsCharactersBetweenAllVisiblePositions);
2109 return findClosestPlainText(*searchRange, matchText, { }, targetOffset);
2110}

2112static bool isReplacedNodeOrBR(Node* node)
2113{
2114 return node && (AccessibilityObject::replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(node) || node->hasTagName(brTag));
2115}
2116
2117static bool characterOffsetsInOrder(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset1, const CharacterOffset& characterOffset2)
2118{
2119 // FIXME: Should just be able to call treeOrder without accessibility-specific logic.
2120 // FIXME: Not clear why CharacterOffset needs to exist at all; we have both Position and BoundaryPoint to choose from.
2121
2122 if (characterOffset1.isNull() || characterOffset2.isNull())
2123 return false;
2124
2125 if (characterOffset1.node == characterOffset2.node)
2126 return characterOffset1.offset <= characterOffset2.offset;
2127
2128 Node* node1 = characterOffset1.node;
2129 Node* node2 = characterOffset2.node;
2130 if (!node1->isCharacterDataNode() && !isReplacedNodeOrBR(node1) && node1->hasChildNodes())
2131 node1 = node1->traverseToChildAt(characterOffset1.offset);
2132 if (!node2->isCharacterDataNode() && !isReplacedNodeOrBR(node2) && node2->hasChildNodes())
2133 node2 = node2->traverseToChildAt(characterOffset2.offset);
2134 if (!node1 || !node2)
2135 return false;
2136
2137 auto range1 = AXObjectCache::rangeForNodeContents(*node1);
2138 auto range2 = AXObjectCache::rangeForNodeContents(*node2);
2139 return is_lteq(treeOrder<ComposedTree>(range1.start, range2.start));
2140}

2142static Node* resetNodeAndOffsetForReplacedNode(Node& replacedNode, int& offset, int characterCount)
2143{
2144 // Use this function to include the replaced node itself in the range we are creating.
2145 auto nodeRange = AXObjectCache::rangeForNodeContents(replacedNode);
2146 bool isInNode = static_cast<unsigned>(characterCount) <= WebCore::characterCount(nodeRange);
2147 offset = replacedNode.computeNodeIndex() + (isInNode ? 0 : 1);
2148 return replacedNode.parentNode();
2149}
2150
2151static std::optional<BoundaryPoint> boundaryPoint(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset, bool isStart)
2152{
2153 if (characterOffset.isNull())
2154 return std::nullopt;
2155
2156 int offset = characterOffset.startIndex + characterOffset.offset;
2157 Node* node = characterOffset.node;
2158 ASSERT(node);
2159
2160 bool replacedNodeOrBR = isReplacedNodeOrBR(node);
2161 // For the non text node that has no children, we should create the range with its parent, otherwise the range would be collapsed.
2162 // Example: <div contenteditable="true"></div>, we want the range to include the div element.
2163 bool noChildren = !replacedNodeOrBR && !node->isTextNode() && !node->hasChildNodes();
2164 int characterCount = noChildren ? (isStart ? 0 : 1) : characterOffset.offset;
2165
2166 if (replacedNodeOrBR || noChildren)
2167 node = resetNodeAndOffsetForReplacedNode(*node, offset, characterCount);
2168
2169 if (!node)
2170 return std::nullopt;
2171
2172 return { { *node, static_cast<unsigned>(offset) } };
2173}
2174
2175static bool setRangeStartOrEndWithCharacterOffset(SimpleRange& range, const CharacterOffset& characterOffset, bool isStart)
2176{
2177 auto point = boundaryPoint(characterOffset, isStart);
2178 if (!point)
2179 return false;
2180 if (isStart)
2181 range.start = *point;
2182 else
2183 range.end = *point;
2184 return true;
2185}

2187std::optional<SimpleRange> AXObjectCache::rangeForUnorderedCharacterOffsets(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset1, const CharacterOffset& characterOffset2)
2188{
2189 bool alreadyInOrder = characterOffsetsInOrder(characterOffset1, characterOffset2);
2190 auto start = boundaryPoint(alreadyInOrder ? characterOffset1 : characterOffset2, true);
2191 auto end = boundaryPoint(alreadyInOrder ? characterOffset2 : characterOffset1, false);
2192 if (!start || !end)
2193 return std::nullopt;
2194 return { { *start, * end } };

2230CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(const SimpleRange& range, bool isStart, bool enterTextControls)
2231{
2232 // When getting the end CharacterOffset at node boundary, we don't want to collapse to the previous node.
2233 if (!isStart && !range.end.offset)
2234 return characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(range.end.container, 0, TraverseOptionIncludeStart);
2235
2236 // If it's end text marker, we want to go to the end of the range, and stay within the range.
2237 bool stayWithinRange = !isStart;
2238
2239 Node& endNode = range.end.container;
2240 if (endNode.isCharacterDataNode() && !isStart)
2241 return traverseToOffsetInRange(rangeForNodeContents(endNode), range.end.offset, TraverseOptionValidateOffset);
2242
2243 auto copyRange = range;
2244 // Change the start of the range, so the character offset starts from node beginning.
2245 int offset = 0;
2246 auto& node = copyRange.start.container.get();
2247 if (node.isCharacterDataNode()) {
2248 auto nodeStartOffset = traverseToOffsetInRange(rangeForNodeContents(node), range.start.offset, TraverseOptionValidateOffset);
2249 if (isStart)
2250 return nodeStartOffset;
2251 copyRange.start.offset = 0;
2252 offset += nodeStartOffset.offset;
2253 }
2254
2255 auto options = isStart ? TraverseOptionDefault : TraverseOptionToNodeEnd;
2256 if (!enterTextControls)
2257 options = static_cast<TraverseOption>(options | TraverseOptionDoNotEnterTextControls);
2258 return traverseToOffsetInRange(copyRange, offset, options, stayWithinRange);
2259}

2273
2274CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(Node& node, int offset, TraverseOption option)
2275{
2276 Node* domNode = &node;
2277 if (!domNode)
2278 return CharacterOffset();
2279
2280 bool toNodeEnd = option & TraverseOptionToNodeEnd;
2281 bool includeStart = option & TraverseOptionIncludeStart;
2282
2283 // ignoreStart is used to determine if we should go to previous node or
2284 // stay in current node when offset is 0.
2285 if (!toNodeEnd && (offset < 0 || (!offset && !includeStart))) {
2286 // Set the offset to the amount of characters we need to go backwards.
2287 offset = - offset;
2288 CharacterOffset charOffset = CharacterOffset();
2289 while (offset >= 0 && charOffset.offset <= offset) {
2290 offset -= charOffset.offset;
2291 domNode = previousNode(domNode);
2292 if (domNode) {
2293 charOffset = characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(*domNode, 0, TraverseOptionToNodeEnd);
2294 } else
2295 return CharacterOffset();
2296 if (charOffset.offset == offset)
2297 break;
2298 }
2299 if (offset > 0)
2300 charOffset = characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(*charOffset.node, charOffset.offset - offset, TraverseOptionIncludeStart);
2301 return charOffset;
2302 }
2303
2304 auto range = rangeForNodeContents(*domNode);
2305
2306 // Traverse the offset amount of characters forward and see if there's remaining offsets.
2307 // Keep traversing to the next node when there's remaining offsets.
2308 CharacterOffset characterOffset = traverseToOffsetInRange(range, offset, option);
2309 while (!characterOffset.isNull() && characterOffset.remaining() && !toNodeEnd) {
2310 domNode = nextNode(domNode);
2311 if (!domNode)
2312 return CharacterOffset();
2313 range = rangeForNodeContents(*domNode);
2314 characterOffset = traverseToOffsetInRange(range, characterOffset.remaining(), option);
2315 }
2316
2317 return characterOffset;
2318}

2329bool AXObjectCache::shouldSkipBoundary(const CharacterOffset& previous, const CharacterOffset& next)
2330{
2331 // Match the behavior of VisiblePosition, we should skip the node boundary when there's no visual space or new line character.
2332 if (previous.isNull() || next.isNull())
2333 return false;
2334
2335 if (previous.node == next.node)
2336 return false;
2337
2338 if (next.startIndex > 0 || next.offset > 0)
2339 return false;
2340
2341 CharacterOffset newLine = startCharacterOffsetOfLine(next);
2342 if (next.isEqual(newLine))
2343 return false;
2344
2345 return true;
2346}

2348void AXObjectCache::textMarkerDataForNextCharacterOffset(TextMarkerData& textMarkerData, const CharacterOffset& characterOffset)
2349{
2350 CharacterOffset next = characterOffset;
2351 CharacterOffset previous = characterOffset;
2352 bool shouldContinue;
2353 do {
2354 shouldContinue = false;
2355 next = nextCharacterOffset(next, false);
2356 if (shouldSkipBoundary(previous, next))
2357 next = nextCharacterOffset(next, false);
2358 textMarkerDataForCharacterOffset(textMarkerData, next);
2359
2360 // We should skip next CharacterOffset if it's visually the same.
2361 if (!lengthForRange(rangeForUnorderedCharacterOffsets(previous, next)))
2362 shouldContinue = true;
2363 previous = next;
2364 } while (textMarkerData.ignored || shouldContinue);
2365}

2373 shouldContinue = false;

2375 textMarkerDataForCharacterOffset(textMarkerData, previous);
2376
2377 // We should skip previous CharacterOffset if it's visually the same.
2378 if (!lengthForRange(rangeForUnorderedCharacterOffsets(previous, next)))
2379 shouldContinue = true;
2380 next = previous;
2381 } while (textMarkerData.ignored || shouldContinue);

2416
2417CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::characterOffsetFromVisiblePosition(const VisiblePosition& visiblePos)
2418{
2419 if (visiblePos.isNull())
2420 return CharacterOffset();
2421
2422 Position deepPos = visiblePos.deepEquivalent();
2423 Node* domNode = deepPos.deprecatedNode();
2424 ASSERT(domNode);
2425
2426 if (domNode->isCharacterDataNode())
2427 return traverseToOffsetInRange(rangeForNodeContents(*domNode), deepPos.deprecatedEditingOffset(), TraverseOptionValidateOffset);
2428
2429 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> obj = this->getOrCreate(domNode);
2430 if (!obj)
2431 return CharacterOffset();
2432
2433 // Use nextVisiblePosition to calculate how many characters we need to traverse to the current position.
2434 VisiblePositionRange visiblePositionRange = obj->visiblePositionRange();
2435 VisiblePosition visiblePosition = visiblePositionRange.start;
2436 int characterOffset = 0;
2437 Position currentPosition = visiblePosition.deepEquivalent();
2438
2439 VisiblePosition previousVisiblePos;
2440 while (!currentPosition.isNull() && !deepPos.equals(currentPosition)) {
2441 previousVisiblePos = visiblePosition;
2442 visiblePosition = obj->nextVisiblePosition(visiblePosition);
2443 currentPosition = visiblePosition.deepEquivalent();
2444 Position previousPosition = previousVisiblePos.deepEquivalent();
2445 // Sometimes nextVisiblePosition will give the same VisiblePostion,
2446 // we break here to avoid infinite loop.
2447 if (currentPosition.equals(previousPosition))
2448 break;
2449 characterOffset++;
2450
2451 // When VisiblePostion moves to next node, it will count the leading line break as
2452 // 1 offset, which we shouldn't include in CharacterOffset.
2453 if (currentPosition.deprecatedNode() != previousPosition.deprecatedNode()) {
2454 if (visiblePosition.characterBefore() == '\n')
2455 characterOffset--;
2456 } else {
2457 // Sometimes VisiblePosition will move multiple characters, like emoji.
2458 if (currentPosition.deprecatedNode()->isCharacterDataNode())
2459 characterOffset += currentPosition.offsetInContainerNode() - previousPosition.offsetInContainerNode() - 1;
2460 }
2461 }
2462
2463 // Sometimes when the node is a replaced node and is ignored in accessibility, we get a wrong CharacterOffset from it.
2464 CharacterOffset result = traverseToOffsetInRange(rangeForNodeContents(*obj->node()), characterOffset);
2465 if (result.remainingOffset > 0 && !result.isNull() && isRendererReplacedElement(result.node->renderer()))
2466 result.offset += result.remainingOffset;
2467 return result;
2468}

2553CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::nextCharacterOffset(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset, bool ignoreNextNodeStart)
2554{
2555 if (characterOffset.isNull())
2556 return CharacterOffset();
2557
2558 // We don't always move one 'character' at a time since there might be composed characters.
2559 unsigned nextOffset = Position::uncheckedNextOffset(characterOffset.node, characterOffset.offset);
2560 CharacterOffset next = characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(*characterOffset.node, nextOffset);
2561
2562 // To be consistent with VisiblePosition, we should consider the case that current node end to next node start counts 1 offset.
2563 if (!ignoreNextNodeStart && !next.isNull() && !isReplacedNodeOrBR(next.node) && next.node != characterOffset.node) {
2564 if (auto range = rangeForUnorderedCharacterOffsets(characterOffset, next)) {
2565 auto length = characterCount(*range);
2566 if (length > nextOffset - characterOffset.offset)
2567 next = characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(*next.node, 0, TraverseOptionIncludeStart);
2568 }
2569 }
2570
2571 return next;
2572}

2578

2580 if (!ignorePreviousNodeEnd && !characterOffset.offset)
2581 return characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(*characterOffset.node, 0);

2588CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::startCharacterOffsetOfWord(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset, EWordSide side)
2589{
2590 if (characterOffset.isNull())
2591 return CharacterOffset();
2592
2593 CharacterOffset c = characterOffset;
2594 if (side == RightWordIfOnBoundary) {
2595 CharacterOffset endOfParagraph = endCharacterOffsetOfParagraph(c);
2596 if (c.isEqual(endOfParagraph))
2597 return c;
2598
2599 // We should consider the node boundary that splits words. Otherwise VoiceOver won't see it as space.
2600 c = nextCharacterOffset(characterOffset, false);
2601 if (shouldSkipBoundary(characterOffset, c))
2602 c = nextCharacterOffset(c, false);
2603 if (c.isNull())
2604 return characterOffset;
2605 }
2606
2607 return previousBoundary(c, startWordBoundary);
2608}

2610CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::endCharacterOffsetOfWord(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset, EWordSide side)
2611{
2612 if (characterOffset.isNull())
2613 return CharacterOffset();
2614
2615 CharacterOffset c = characterOffset;
2616 if (side == LeftWordIfOnBoundary) {
2617 CharacterOffset startOfParagraph = startCharacterOffsetOfParagraph(c);
2618 if (c.isEqual(startOfParagraph))
2619 return c;
2620
2621 c = previousCharacterOffset(characterOffset);
2622 if (c.isNull())
2623 return characterOffset;
2624 } else {
2625 CharacterOffset endOfParagraph = endCharacterOffsetOfParagraph(characterOffset);
2626 if (characterOffset.isEqual(endOfParagraph))
2627 return characterOffset;
2628 }
2629
2630 return nextBoundary(c, endWordBoundary);
2631}

2705static Node* parentEditingBoundary(Node* node)
2706{
2707 if (!node)
2708 return nullptr;
2709
2710 Node* documentElement = node->document().documentElement();
2711 if (!documentElement)
2712 return nullptr;
2713
2714 Node* boundary = node;
2715 while (boundary != documentElement && boundary->nonShadowBoundaryParentNode() && node->hasEditableStyle() == boundary->parentNode()->hasEditableStyle())
2716 boundary = boundary->nonShadowBoundaryParentNode();
2717
2718 return boundary;
2719}
2720
2721CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::nextBoundary(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset, BoundarySearchFunction searchFunction)
2722{
2723 if (characterOffset.isNull())
2724 return { };
2725
2726 Node* boundary = parentEditingBoundary(characterOffset.node);
2727 if (!boundary)
2728 return { };
2729
2730 auto searchRange = rangeForNodeContents(*boundary);
2731
2732 Vector<UChar, 1024> string;
2733 unsigned prefixLength = 0;
2734
2735 if (requiresContextForWordBoundary(characterAfter(characterOffset))) {
2736 auto backwardsScanRange = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(boundary->document());
2737 if (!setRangeStartOrEndWithCharacterOffset(backwardsScanRange, characterOffset, false))
2738 return { };
2739 prefixLength = prefixLengthForRange(backwardsScanRange, string);
2740 }
2741
2742 if (!setRangeStartOrEndWithCharacterOffset(searchRange, characterOffset, true))
2743 return { };
2744 CharacterOffset end = startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(searchRange, false);
2745
2746 TextIterator it(searchRange, TextIteratorBehavior::EmitsObjectReplacementCharacters);
2747 unsigned next = forwardSearchForBoundaryWithTextIterator(it, string, prefixLength, searchFunction);
2748
2749 if (it.atEnd() && next == string.size())
2750 return end;
2751
2752 // We should consider the node boundary that splits words.
2753 if (searchFunction == endWordBoundary && next - prefixLength == 1)
2754 return nextCharacterOffset(characterOffset, false);
2755
2756 // The endSentenceBoundary function will include a line break at the end of the sentence.
2757 if (searchFunction == endSentenceBoundary && string[next - 1] == '\n')
2758 next--;
2759
2760 if (next > prefixLength)
2761 return characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(*characterOffset.node, characterOffset.offset + next - prefixLength);
2762
2763 return characterOffset;
2764}

2766// FIXME: Share code with the one in VisibleUnits.cpp.
2767CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::previousBoundary(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset, BoundarySearchFunction searchFunction, NeedsContextAtParagraphStart needsContextAtParagraphStart)
2768{
2769 if (characterOffset.isNull())
2770 return CharacterOffset();
2771
2772 Node* boundary = parentEditingBoundary(characterOffset.node);
2773 if (!boundary)
2774 return CharacterOffset();
2775
2776 auto searchRange = rangeForNodeContents(*boundary);
2777 Vector<UChar, 1024> string;
2778 unsigned suffixLength = 0;
2779
2780 if (needsContextAtParagraphStart == NeedsContextAtParagraphStart::Yes && startCharacterOffsetOfParagraph(characterOffset).isEqual(characterOffset)) {
2781 auto forwardsScanRange = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(boundary->document());
2782 auto endOfCurrentParagraph = endCharacterOffsetOfParagraph(characterOffset);
2783 if (!setRangeStartOrEndWithCharacterOffset(forwardsScanRange, characterOffset, true))
2784 return { };
2785 if (!setRangeStartOrEndWithCharacterOffset(forwardsScanRange, endOfCurrentParagraph, false))
2786 return { };
2787 for (TextIterator forwardsIterator(forwardsScanRange); !forwardsIterator.atEnd(); forwardsIterator.advance())
2788 append(string, forwardsIterator.text());
2789 suffixLength = string.size();
2790 } else if (requiresContextForWordBoundary(characterBefore(characterOffset))) {
2791 auto forwardsScanRange = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(boundary->document());
2792 auto afterBoundary = makeBoundaryPointAfterNode(*boundary);
2793 if (!afterBoundary)
2794 return { };
2795 forwardsScanRange.start = *afterBoundary;
2796 if (!setRangeStartOrEndWithCharacterOffset(forwardsScanRange, characterOffset, true))
2797 return { };
2798 suffixLength = suffixLengthForRange(forwardsScanRange, string);
2799 }
2800
2801 if (!setRangeStartOrEndWithCharacterOffset(searchRange, characterOffset, false))
2802 return { };
2803 CharacterOffset start = startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(searchRange, true);
2804
2805 SimplifiedBackwardsTextIterator it(searchRange);
2806 unsigned next = backwardSearchForBoundaryWithTextIterator(it, string, suffixLength, searchFunction);
2807
2808 if (!next)
2809 return it.atEnd() ? start : characterOffset;
2810
2811 auto& node = (it.atEnd() ? searchRange : it.range()).start.container.get();
2812
2813 // SimplifiedBackwardsTextIterator ignores replaced elements.
2814 if (AccessibilityObject::replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(characterOffset.node))
2815 return characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(*characterOffset.node, 0);
2816 Node* nextSibling = node.nextSibling();
2817 if (&node != characterOffset.node && AccessibilityObject::replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(nextSibling))
2818 return startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(rangeForNodeContents(*nextSibling), false);
2819
2820 if ((!suffixLength && node.isTextNode() && next <= node.length()) || (node.renderer() && node.renderer()->isBR() && !next)) {
2821 // The next variable contains a usable index into a text node
2822 if (node.isTextNode())
2823 return traverseToOffsetInRange(rangeForNodeContents(node), next, TraverseOptionValidateOffset);
2824 return characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(node, next, TraverseOptionIncludeStart);
2825 }
2826
2827 int characterCount = characterOffset.offset;
2828 if (next < string.size() - suffixLength)
2829 characterCount -= string.size() - suffixLength - next;
2830 // We don't want to go to the previous node if the node is at the start of a new line.
2831 if (characterCount < 0 && (characterOffsetNodeIsBR(characterOffset) || string[string.size() - suffixLength - 1] == '\n'))
2832 characterCount = 0;
2833 return characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(*characterOffset.node, characterCount, TraverseOptionIncludeStart);
2834}

2836CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::startCharacterOffsetOfParagraph(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset, EditingBoundaryCrossingRule boundaryCrossingRule)
2837{
2838 if (characterOffset.isNull())
2839 return CharacterOffset();
2840
2841 auto& startNode = *characterOffset.node;
2842
2843 if (isRenderedAsNonInlineTableImageOrHR(&startNode))
2844 return startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(rangeForNodeContents(startNode), true);
2845
2846 auto* startBlock = enclosingBlock(&startNode);
2847 int offset = characterOffset.startIndex + characterOffset.offset;
2848 auto* highestRoot = highestEditableRoot(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(&startNode));
2849 Position::AnchorType type = Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor;
2850
2851 auto& node = *findStartOfParagraph(&startNode, highestRoot, startBlock, offset, type, boundaryCrossingRule);
2852
2853 if (type == Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor)
2854 return characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(node, offset, TraverseOptionIncludeStart);
2855
2856 return startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(rangeForNodeContents(node), true);
2857}
2858
2859CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::endCharacterOffsetOfParagraph(const CharacterOffset& characterOffset, EditingBoundaryCrossingRule boundaryCrossingRule)
2860{
2861 if (characterOffset.isNull())
2862 return CharacterOffset();
2863
2864 Node* startNode = characterOffset.node;
2865 if (isRenderedAsNonInlineTableImageOrHR(startNode))
2866 return startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(rangeForNodeContents(*startNode), false);
2867
2868 Node* stayInsideBlock = enclosingBlock(startNode);
2869 int offset = characterOffset.startIndex + characterOffset.offset;
2870 Node* highestRoot = highestEditableRoot(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(startNode));
2871 Position::AnchorType type = Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor;
2872
2873 auto& node = *findEndOfParagraph(startNode, highestRoot, stayInsideBlock, offset, type, boundaryCrossingRule);
2874 if (type == Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor) {
2875 if (node.isTextNode()) {
2876 CharacterOffset startOffset = startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(rangeForNodeContents(node), true);
2877 offset -= startOffset.startIndex;
2878 }
2879 return characterOffsetForNodeAndOffset(node, offset, TraverseOptionIncludeStart);
2880 }
2881
2882 return startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(rangeForNodeContents(node), false);
2883}

3007CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::characterOffsetForBounds(const IntRect& rect, bool first)
3008{
3009 if (rect.isEmpty())
3010 return CharacterOffset();
3011
3012 IntPoint corner = first ? rect.minXMinYCorner() : rect.maxXMaxYCorner();
3013 CharacterOffset characterOffset = characterOffsetForPoint(corner);
3014
3015 if (rect.contains(absoluteCaretBoundsForCharacterOffset(characterOffset).center()))
3016 return characterOffset;
3017
3018 // If the initial position is located outside the bounds adjust it incrementally as needed.
3019 CharacterOffset nextCharOffset = nextCharacterOffset(characterOffset, false);
3020 CharacterOffset previousCharOffset = previousCharacterOffset(characterOffset, false);
3021 while (!nextCharOffset.isNull() || !previousCharOffset.isNull()) {
3022 if (rect.contains(absoluteCaretBoundsForCharacterOffset(nextCharOffset).center()))
3023 return nextCharOffset;
3024 if (rect.contains(absoluteCaretBoundsForCharacterOffset(previousCharOffset).center()))
3025 return previousCharOffset;
3026
3027 nextCharOffset = nextCharacterOffset(nextCharOffset, false);
3028 previousCharOffset = previousCharacterOffset(previousCharOffset, false);
3029 }
3030
3031 return CharacterOffset();
3032}

3057CharacterOffset AXObjectCache::characterOffsetForIndex(int index, const AXCoreObject* obj)
3058{
3059 if (!obj)
3060 return CharacterOffset();
3061
3062 VisiblePosition vp = obj->visiblePositionForIndex(index);
3063 CharacterOffset validate = characterOffsetFromVisiblePosition(vp);
3064 // In text control, VisiblePosition always gives the before position of a
3065 // BR node, while CharacterOffset will do the opposite.
3066 if (obj->isTextControl() && characterOffsetNodeIsBR(validate))
3067 validate.offset = 1;
3068
3069 auto liveRange = obj->elementRange();
3070 if (!liveRange)
3071 return { };
3072
3073 auto range = SimpleRange { *liveRange };
3074 CharacterOffset start = startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(range, true, true);
3075 CharacterOffset end = startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(range, false, true);
3076 CharacterOffset result = start;
3077 for (int i = 0; i < index; i++) {
3078 if (result.isEqual(validate)) {
3079 // Do not include the new line character, always move the offset to the start of next node.
3080 if ((validate.node->isTextNode() || characterOffsetNodeIsBR(validate))) {
3081 CharacterOffset next = nextCharacterOffset(validate, false);
3082 if (!next.isNull() && !next.offset && rootAXEditableElement(next.node) == rootAXEditableElement(validate.node))
3083 result = next;
3084 }
3085 break;
3086 }
3087
3088 result = nextCharacterOffset(result, false);
3089 if (result.isEqual(end))
3090 break;
3091 }
3092 return result;
3093}

3306void AXObjectCache::updateIsolatedTree(const Vector<std::pair<RefPtr<AXCoreObject>, AXNotification>>& notifications)
3307{
3308 AXTRACE("AXObjectCache::updateIsolatedTree");
3309 AXLOG(*this);
3310
3311 if (!m_pageID) {
3312 AXLOG("No pageID.");
3313 return;
3314 }
3315

3317 if (!tree) {
3318 AXLOG("No isolated tree for m_pageID");
3319 return;
3320 }
3321
3322 // Filter out multiple notifications for the same object. This avoids
3323 // updating the isolated tree multiple times unnecessarily.
3324 Vector<std::pair<RefPtr<AXCoreObject>, AXNotification>> filteredNotifications;
3325 for (const auto& notification : notifications) {
3326 AXLOG(notification);
3327 if (!notification.first || notification.first->objectID() == InvalidAXID)

3330 switch (notification.second) {
3331 case AXAriaRoleChanged:
3332 tree->updateNode(*notification.first);
3333 break;
3334 case AXCheckedStateChanged:
3335 tree->updateNodeProperty(*notification.first, AXPropertyName::IsChecked);
3336 break;
3337 case AXSortDirectionChanged:
3338 tree->updateNodeProperty(*notification.first, AXPropertyName::SortDirection);
3339 break;
3340 case AXIdAttributeChanged:
3341 tree->updateNodeProperty(*notification.first, AXPropertyName::IdentifierAttribute);
3342 break;
3343 case AXActiveDescendantChanged:
3344 case AXSelectedChildrenChanged:
3345 case AXSelectedTextChanged:
3346 case AXValueChanged: {
3347 bool needsUpdate = appendIfNotContainsMatching(filteredNotifications, notification, [&notification] (const std::pair<RefPtr<AXCoreObject>, AXNotification>& note) {
3348 return note.second == notification.second && note.first.get() == notification.first.get();
3349 });
3350
3351 if (needsUpdate)
3352 tree->updateNode(*notification.first);
3353 break;
3354 }
3355 case AXChildrenChanged:
3356 case AXLanguageChanged:
3357 case AXRowCountChanged:
3358 case AXRowCollapsed:
3359 case AXRowExpanded:
3360 case AXExpandedChanged: {
3361 bool needsUpdate = appendIfNotContainsMatching(filteredNotifications, notification, [&notification] (const std::pair<RefPtr<AXCoreObject>, AXNotification>& note) {
3362 return note.second == notification.second && note.first.get() == notification.first.get();
3363 });

3365 if (needsUpdate)
3366 tree->updateChildren(*notification.first);

3427
3428bool isNodeAriaVisible(Node* node)
3429{
3430 if (!node)
3431 return false;
3432
3433 // If an element is focused, it should not be hidden.
3434 if (is<Element>(*node) && downcast<Element>(*node).focused())
3435 return true;
3436
3437 // ARIA Node visibility is controlled by aria-hidden
3438 // 1) if aria-hidden=true, the whole subtree is hidden
3439 // 2) if aria-hidden=false, and the object is rendered, there's no effect
3440 // 3) if aria-hidden=false, and the object is NOT rendered, then it must have
3441 // aria-hidden=false on each parent until it gets to a rendered object
3442 // 3b) a text node inherits a parents aria-hidden value
3443 bool requiresAriaHiddenFalse = !node->renderer();
3444 bool ariaHiddenFalsePresent = false;
3445 for (Node* testNode = node; testNode; testNode = testNode->parentNode()) {
3446 if (is<Element>(*testNode)) {
3447 const AtomString& ariaHiddenValue = downcast<Element>(*testNode).attributeWithoutSynchronization(aria_hiddenAttr);
3448 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(ariaHiddenValue, "true"))
3449 return false;
3450
3451 // We should break early when it gets to the body.
3452 if (testNode->hasTagName(bodyTag))
3453 break;
3454
3455 bool ariaHiddenFalse = equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(ariaHiddenValue, "false");
3456 if (!testNode->renderer() && !ariaHiddenFalse)
3457 return false;
3458 if (!ariaHiddenFalsePresent && ariaHiddenFalse)
3459 ariaHiddenFalsePresent = true;
3460 }
3461 }
3462
3463 return !requiresAriaHiddenFalse || ariaHiddenFalsePresent;
3464}

3466AccessibilityObject* AXObjectCache::rootWebArea()
3467{
3468 auto* root = getOrCreate(m_document.view());
3469 if (!root || !root->isScrollView())
3470 return nullptr;
3471 return root->webAreaObject();
3472}
